StudyLink:
Description: StudyLink is a university-focused study group platform that allows students to create, discover, and join course-based study groups. The system supports real-time group chat, session scheduling, and member management within a structured academic environment.

Features:
- User Authentication with University Email
- Create and join public/private study groups
- Real-time group chat system
- Study session scheduling
- Profile Management
- Admin panel for moderation and system oversight.

Tech Stack:
- HTML, CSS (Custom + Bootstrap), and Figma (UI Design & Prototyping)

Project Structure:
/project-root
|-- readme
|-- admin.html
|-- dashboard.html
|-- find-groups.html
|-- group-chat.html
|-- login.html
|-- profile.html
|-- register.html
|-- style.css

Design Approach:
The interface was designed using the medium-fidelity prototypes created in Figma, as well as low-fidelity sketches of the website. The design emphasizes:
- Consistency across pages
- Clear navigation
- Familiar interaction patterns
- Minimal cognitive load for users.

Here is the link to the medium fidelity design on Figma. 
https://www.figma.com/design/zaLT85VwLA2Q1AJrrNk42k/ITEC-3230-Mid-Fid?node-id=0-1&t=JK1Pe6uCDaX1AHgq-1

*NOTE: This project is a front-end prototype developed for ITEC 3230 COURSE. Some features are simulated and do not include full backend functionality. 
